[Student "S"]
{You do have 9 points, of a sort anyway. Hoping your \C suit will be of use, you invite with 2NT. Partner says 3NT.

The contract would be 3NT played by East.

West plays 3NT. North leads the \SQ, South following with the \S2. Do you hold up or not?

Winner List: \S = 2 : \H = 1 : \D = 1 : \C = 1 :: Total = 5

No, don't hold up. At least you have \Ss stopped twice, your other suits are stopped only once.

Realizing that your only hope is for a bunch of \C tricks you win the \SK and play the \CQ. North covers with the \CK. What do you do? 

If you win with dummy's \CA, and if the \Cs split 2-2, you can win 7 \C tricks and 4 other high cards. Wow! 

But if it turns out that the \CK was singleton you will win just TWO \C tricks because dummy has no other entries. 

So if you feel like gambling, go up with the \CA. But if you like the idea of a guaranteed contract let North hold the \CK, and you make sure of the six other \Cs.

This Deal is not a "made up" one, it was actually played at our Monday Duplicate game in May 2012.

The play went exactly as shown above. When her LHO played the \CK our declarer ducked in dummy and made the contract.}
[Play "W"]SQ

